cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the design and implementation of a novel architecture for future mobile communication systems. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the decoupling of signaling and data at the air interface to mitigate signaling overhead, which involves information theory concepts. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may discuss security issues related to the proposed hyper-cellular network architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the control and management of the hyper-cellular network. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed concept on a software defined radio platform.
